Date: Tue, 30 Nov 2010 06:38:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 176/271] net: Fix too optimistic NETIF_F_HW_CSUM features
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 7903264402546f45f9bac8ad2bfdb00d00eb124a
Patch-mainline: v2.6.38-rc1
References: FATE#311458 FATE#311459 FATE#311460 FATE#311461 FATE#311462 bnc#698050

Upstream commit: 7903264402546f45f9bac8ad2bfdb00d00eb124a

NETIF_F_HW_CSUM is a superset of NETIF_F_IP_CSUM+NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM, but
some drivers miss the difference. Fix this and also fix UFO dependency
on checksumming offload as it makes the same mistake in assumptions.

Signed-off-by: Michał Mirosław <mirq-linux@rere.qmqm.pl>
Acked-by: Jon Mason <jon.mason@exar.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c b/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
index 31d31ad..3cf6339 100644
--- a/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
@@ -8897,7 +8897,7 @@ static int __devinit bnx2x_init_dev(struct pci_dev *pdev,
 	dev->netdev_ops = &bnx2x_netdev_ops;
 	bnx2x_set_ethtool_ops(dev);
 	dev->features |= NETIF_F_SG;
-	dev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_CSUM;
+	dev->features |= NETIF_F_IP_CSUM | NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM;
 	if (bp->flags & USING_DAC_FLAG)
 		dev->features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
 	dev->features |= (NETIF_F_TSO | NETIF_F_TSO_ECN);
@@ -8907,7 +8907,7 @@ static int __devinit bnx2x_init_dev(struct pci_dev *pdev,
 	bp->flags |= (HW_VLAN_RX_FLAG | HW_VLAN_TX_FLAG);
 
 	dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_SG;
-	dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_HW_CSUM;
+	dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_IP_CSUM | NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM;
 	if (bp->flags & USING_DAC_FLAG)
 		dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
 	dev->vlan_features |= (NETIF_F_TSO | NETIF_F_TSO_ECN);
